<h2 style="color:white">Coconut Shells</h2>
<div style="color:white">This product is 100% natural and bio-degradable, making it significantly better for the environment. Ninety-nine percent of coconut shells are gone to waste every year, when they could easily be turned into amazing bowls</div>
<img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0244/1931/products/bambu_coconut_bowl_natural.jpg?v=1571266863"
alt="coconut shells"
style="width:300px; height: 200px">
<hr>
<h3> <div style="color:white"> There are several good aspects of using coconut shells into bowls.</h3>
<h4 style="color:white">1. They are made from a recycled waste product</h4>
<div style="color:white">Coconut Shells are being wasted for no reason, when they can easily be turned into our everyday tools like bowls. Otherwise these coconut shells would just be burned or sent to the landfill.
<img
src="https://c8.alamy.com/comp/M8E0K9/a-large-pile-of-coconut-husks-at-a-coconut-farm-vietnam-M8E0K9.jpg"
alt="Wasted Shells"
style="width:300px; height: 200px">
<hr>
<h4 style="color:white">2. They create jobs </h4>
<h5 style="color:white"> In many countries there are not enough jobs for the people living there. Turning these shells into bowls creates a lot more opportunites for people to earn money around the world, and by buying them you are supporting those in need.</h5>
<img
src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSvVWfuOYXBldWywfBng6AvBOTZlv6uNG7Lkw&usqp=CAU"
alt="shell jobs"
style="width:300px; height: 200px">
<hr>

</style>
<h4 style="color:white"> 3. They create zero waste </h4>
<div style="color:white">Coconut Shells will cause no harm to the environment, they are biodegradable and will not pollute our oceans or harm our wildlife, unlike plastic bowls.
